From: art-suite conda packaging
Subject: [PATCH] Add missing <algorithm> includes for std::any_of / std::find_if etc.

Several art sources call std::any_of / std::all_of / std::find_if / std::transform
and similar <algorithm> functions but rely on the header being pulled in
transitively. Older libstdc++ provided it indirectly; conda-forge's newer
libstdc++ does not, so the build fails (e.g. Selector.h: "'any_of' is not a
member of 'std'"). Add the missing direct includes (IWYU). Only the non-test
TUs are touched (BUILD_TESTING=OFF). See conda/potential_improvements.md.

--- a/art/Framework/Art/detail/get_LibraryInfoCollection.cc	2026-06-19 12:30:12.019867901 -0700
